This paper analyzes the geographical distribution of biomedical research in the USA and China using K-means clustering. The analysis involves a large amount of geocoded data and focuses on the centralization of research hubs. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DL (Digital Libraries) which deals with the organization, retrieval, and distribution of digital information. Other likely categories include cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) which deals with the analysis of social networks and their impact on information dissemination, cs.IR (Information Retrieval) which deals with the retrieval of relevant information from large datasets, cs.SOC (Social and Economic Networks) which deals with the analysis of social and economic networks, and cs.CYBER (Cybersecurity) which deals with the protection of digital information.
